g you for a second look a little ballad you turned down in 1953.1 I still think it is one of the best things I ever wrote. On second thought—tell me first if I may send it again.

If I find any potential New Yorker contributors in my classes, I shall tell them to go ahead and shall advise you of my discovery.

Véra joins me in sending you both our very kind regards.





Yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: HOWARD NEMEROV

CC, 1 p.

Ithaca, N.Y.





February 18, 1957

